    {
      "type": "standard",
      "output": {
        "generic": [
          {
            "values": [
              {
                "text": "A cyclone or a hurricane is a large, destructive storm that is comprised of strong winds rotating around a center of low pressure. It is often advised to stay home during cyclones"
              }
            ],
            "response_type": "text",
            "selection_policy": "sequential"
          }
        ]
      },
      "conditions": "#Cyclone_About",
      "dialog_node": "node_6_1595699556252",
      "previous_sibling": "node_10_1595699640708"
    },
    {
      "type": "standard",
      "output": {
        "generic": [
          {
            "values": [
              {
                "text": "After the cyclone has passed, devastation often continues. Fallen trees can block roads and delay rescues, with medical supplies, or slow the repairs to electrical lines, telephone towers, or water pipes, which could put other lives at risk for days or months. Stagnant water can cause the spread of disease, and transportation or communication infrastructure may have been destroyed, hampering clean-up and rescue efforts. It is often advised to stay at home."
              }
            ],
            "response_type": "text",
            "selection_policy": "sequential"
          }
        ]
      },
      "conditions": "#Cyclone_After",
      "dialog_node": "node_7_1596043288811",
      "previous_sibling": "node_6_1595699556252"
    },
    {
      "type": "standard",
      "output": {
        "generic": [
          {
            "values": [
              {
                "text": "It is important to stay informed with what is happening and to follow instructions given by emergency officials. If there is a flood warning, find safe shelter right away! Go to a safe location you previously identified. If told to evacuate, do so immediately. Do not walk, swim, or drive through flood waters. Failing to evacuate flooded areas or entering flood waters can result in injury or death. If trapped in a building, get to the highest level. Do not climb into a closed attic and go on the roof only if necessary."
              }
            ],
            "response_type": "text",
            "selection_policy": "sequential"
          }
        ]
      },
      "conditions": "#Flood_During",
      "dialog_node": "node_2_1584231537199",
